Fix zeaz-platform Cloudflare scripts and Terraform zDash integration using official upstream sources:

Sources of truth:
- Cloudflare API docs: https://developers.cloudflare.com/api/
- cloudflared repo: https://github.com/cloudflare/cloudflared
- Terraform Cloudflare provider repo: https://github.com/cloudflare/terraform-provider-cloudflare

Repo:
- cvsz/zeaz-platform
- zDash is integrated under apps/zdash
- zeaz-platform is the Cloudflare operator repo

Problems to fix:
1. Makefile has duplicate tf-zdash-* targets.
2. Terraform has duplicate declarations because old terraform/zdash/zdash_edge.tf exists alongside versions.tf, variables.tf, main.tf, outputs.tf.
3. Terraform plan still reads placeholder values:
   - REPLACE_WITH_ZEAZ_DEV_ZONE_ID
   - REPLACE_WITH_TUNNEL_UUID
4. cf-zdash-preflight fails when CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN is not loaded.
5. Scripts must use scoped CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN only.
6. Do not use Global API Key.
7. Keep no-cost guardrails:
   - COST_LOCK=true
   - CLOUDFLARE_PLAN_TIER=Free
   - ALLOW_PAID_CLOUDFLARE_FEATURES=false
   - ALLOW_LOAD_BALANCING=false
   - ALLOW_ADVANCED_WAF=false
   - ALLOW_LOGPUSH=false
   - ALLOW_R2_WRITE=false
   - ALLOW_WORKERS_DEPLOY=false

Required implementation:

A. Terraform layout
Make terraform/zdash contain only:
- versions.tf
- variables.tf
- main.tf
- outputs.tf
- README.md
- terraform.tfvars.example

Delete:
- terraform/zdash/zdash_edge.tf

versions.tf:
- required_version >= 1.5.0
- provider source cloudflare/cloudflare

variables.tf:
- cloudflare_zone_id validation: 32 lowercase hex chars
- cloudflare_tunnel_id validation: UUID
- zdash_domain default zdash.zeaz.dev
- zdash_api_domain default api-zdash.zeaz.dev
- zdash_release_domain default release.zeaz.dev

main.tf:
- use cloudflare_dns_record.zdash for:
  - zdash.zeaz.dev
  - api-zdash.zeaz.dev
  - release.zeaz.dev
- all CNAME to ${cloudflare_tunnel_id}.cfargotunnel.com
- proxied = true
- ttl = 1

B. Makefile
Remove all existing duplicated blocks for:
- zdash-terraform-integrate
- cf-zdash-preflight
- cf-zdash-import-existing
- tf-zdash-init
- tf-zdash-fmt
- tf-zdash-fmt-check
- tf-zdash-validate
- tf-zdash-plan
- tf-zdash-apply

Add exactly one canonical block:
- zdash-terraform-integrate
- cf-zdash-preflight
- cf-zdash-import-existing
- tf-zdash-init
- tf-zdash-fmt
- tf-zdash-fmt-check
- tf-zdash-validate
- tf-zdash-plan
- tf-zdash-apply

tf-zdash-validate, tf-zdash-plan, tf-zdash-apply must run through:
- scripts/cloudflare/zdash-terraform-env-guard.sh

C. Env guard
Create scripts/cloudflare/zdash-terraform-env-guard.sh:
- fail if terraform/zdash contains placeholder values in any auto-loaded tfvars
- fail if .env.cloudflare.zdash.generated is missing
- source .env.cloudflare.zdash.generated
- fail if TF_VAR_cloudflare_zone_id or TF_VAR_cloudflare_tunnel_id is missing or starts with REPLACE_
- then exec the passed Terraform command

D. Cloudflare API lib
Create/update scripts/cloudflare/cloudflare-api-lib.sh:
- require curl and jq
- require CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN
- reject CLOUDFLARE_API_KEY, CF_API_KEY, GLOBAL_API_KEY, X_AUTH_KEY, CF_GLOBAL_KEY
- provide:
  - cf_api
  - cf_zone_id_by_name
  - cf_dns_record_id
  - cf_validate_zone_id
  - cf_validate_tunnel_uuid
  - cf_cost_lock_check
- use https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4
- never print tokens

E. Preflight
Create/update scripts/cloudflare/zdash-cloudflare-preflight.sh:
- source cloudflare-api-lib.sh
- resolve zone id for zeaz.dev through Cloudflare API if TF_VAR_cloudflare_zone_id is missing
- resolve tunnel UUID from TF_VAR_cloudflare_tunnel_id, or from cloudflared tunnel list if available
- query DNS record IDs for:
  - zdash.zeaz.dev
  - api-zdash.zeaz.dev
  - release.zeaz.dev
- write:
  - docs/reports/generated/zdash-cloudflare-api-preflight.md
  - .env.cloudflare.zdash.generated
- chmod 600 generated env file
- do not commit generated env file

F. Import script
Create/update scripts/cloudflare/zdash-terraform-import-existing.sh:
- requires .env.cloudflare.zdash.generated
- reads Terraform import commands from preflight report
- runs terraform import commands from terraform/zdash
- ignores already-imported errors safely
- tells operator to run make tf-zdash-plan next

G. Generator
Create/update scripts/cloudflare/zdash-terraform-integrate.sh:
- idempotent
- deletes legacy terraform/zdash/zdash_edge.tf
- rewrites the clean Terraform files
- writes docs/reports/generated/zdash-terraform-integration.md
- no Cloudflare mutation

H. Token clean
Keep:
- token-clean = dry-run
- token-clean-delete = live delete only with CONFIRM_TOKEN_DELETE=yes
- default preserve regex must protect:
  - zeaz.dev
  - bootstrap
  - audit
  - admin
  - ai-gateway
- never delete protected tokens by default

I. Validation
Run:
- grep target counts to ensure each tf-zdash target exists exactly once
- test ! -f terraform/zdash/zdash_edge.tf
- make zdash-terraform-integrate
- make yaml-validate
- make workflow-validate
- make phase51-validate
- make phase52-validate
- git diff --check

Acceptance criteria:
- no Makefile override warnings
- no Terraform duplicate required_providers / variable / local / resource errors
- placeholder values fail early with clear env-guard error
- preflight generates .env.cloudflare.zdash.generated only when scoped token exists
- Terraform plan uses real zone/tunnel values from preflight
- no secrets committed
- no .env, .env.cloudflare, .env.cloudflare.zdash.generated, tfstate, tfvars, .terraform committed
